The paper discusses stochastic kernel-based dimensionality reduction approaches, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses the use of user-specified constraints in Markov chains, which is a topic that falls under the category of optimization and control theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SI (Systems and Control).
